                  "title": "2FA not used for email login",
                  "status": "Open",
                  "severity": "Medium",
                  "type": "Linkability",
                  "description": "Without 2FA, malicious actors who gain access to a user's credentials could more easily link the user's activities across different sessions or platforms. If the same credentials are used elsewhere, it becomes easier to link these separate accounts to the same individual, leading to a broader compromise of the user's digital identity.",
