                  "title": "2FA not used for email login",
                  "status": "Open",
                  "severity": "Medium",
                  "type": "Identifiability",
                  "description": "The threat to identifiability increases as stolen credentials can directly identify the user without the added layer of security 2FA provides. With just the password, an attacker can impersonate and identify as the user, accessing sensitive profile information that may include real names, addresses, or other personal data.",
                  "mitigation": "Provide remediation for this threat or a reason if status is N/A",
                  "modelType": "LINDDUN",
