                  "title": "2FA not used for email login",
                  "status": "Open",
                  "severity": "Medium",
                  "type": "Non-repudiation",
                  "description": "If an attacker performs actions using a compromised account, the legitimate user may have a hard time proving they were not the one performing those actions due to the lack of 2FA verification.",
                  "mitigation": "Provide remediation for this threat or a reason if status is N/A",
                  "modelType": "LINDDUN",
                  "new": false,
                  "number": 3,
                  "score": ""
                },
                {
                  "id": "4a327466-7625-456d-8574-9c84bad28b0f",
                  "title": "2FA not used for email login",
                  "status": "Open",
                  "severity": "Medium",
                  "type": "Detectability",
                  "description": "Without 2FA, unauthorized access to an account may go undetected longer, as there's no secondary verification method to alert the user or system to suspicious activity. For instance, a user logging in from an unknown device or location would be a trigger for additional verification, which, if not in place, makes unauthorized access less detectable.",
                  "mitigation": "Provide remediation for this threat or a reason if status is N/A",
                  "modelType": "LINDDUN",
                  "new": false,
                  "number": 4,
