                  "title": "2FA not used for email login",
                  "status": "Open",
                  "severity": "Medium",
                  "type": "Non-compliance",
                  "description": "This can be a threat if the service operates in jurisdictions where strong authentication methods are required by law for certain types of data processing activities. The lack of 2FA might put the service at risk of non-compliance with such regulations, potentially affecting user trust and legal standing.\n\nIn summary, not implementing 2FA can make users of Alovoa more susceptible to privacy breaches due to increased risks of account takeover and identity theft. It also lessens the ability to detect unauthorized access and could impact legal compliance, depending on regulatory requirements. To mitigate these threats, Alovoa would need to implement 2FA and ensure users are aware of the security measures in place.",
